= Choosing our enemies

In our media and campaign materials, who should we consider as our main opponents?

[? if enemies != 0 : Previously, we had considered the [+ enemies +] as our prior enemies. Is a change of direction necessary? ?]

- @anti_dem: The anti-democratic parties of the far right - the DNSAP and GDVP.
- @far_right: The nationalist parties - the CSP, GDVP, DNSAP and LB.
- @nsdap: The DNSAP alone.
- @kpd: The CSP alone.
- @bourgeois: The bourgeois parties - the CSP, LB and GDVP.
- @easy_discard

@anti_dem
on-arrival: enemies = "anti-democratic parties"; center_strength += 5; reformist_strength += 5; left_dissent -= 5; workers_nsdap -= 2; workers_nsdap -= 2; workers_dnvp -= 2

Attacking the far right and left is popular among of our party, who would prefer to be fighting the bourgeois parties.

@far_right
on-arrival: enemies = "far right"; left_strength += 5; left_dissent -= 5; workers_nsdap -= 3; workers_dnvp -= 3; workers_z -= 3; rural_dvp -= 3

Attacking the far right is popular among the entire party, although the left considers the bourgeois parties to be just as dangerous.
@nsdap
on-arrival: enemies = "NSDAP"; neorevisionist_strength += 5; nazi_urgency += 1; workers_nsdap -= 4;

[? if nazi_urgency == 0 or nsdap_r < 10 : The DNSAP is a tiny party right now, with more bark than bite. Many in our party are questioning our choices. ?][? if nazi_urgency > 0 and nsdap_r >= 10 : The Nazis are the most urgent problem for us to deal with. ?]

@kpd
on-arrival: enemies = "KPD"; reformist_strength -= 5; left_dissent -= 8; reformist_dissent += 5; z_relation -= 15; gdvp_relation -= 5; kpd_relation += 5; workers_z -= 4;

Attacking the CSP is supported by all but the reformists, and loses us some measure of approval among the bourgeois parties. However, If we are to reconcile with the CSP, this may not be the best choice.

@bourgeois
on-arrival: enemies = "bourgeois parties"; left_strength += 8; left_dissent -= 5; dvp_relation -= 5; z_relation -= 5; kpd_relation += 5; reformist_dissent += 8; workers_z -= 3; coalition_dissent += 1; workers_dnvp -= 3; rural_dvp -= 3

Our anti-bourgeois rhetoric is popular among the left, but may make it harder to build the coalitions that are necessary for government in the future.
